    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Ireland Is Expected to Scrap The Death Penalty This Year</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">Reuters</byline>
      <dateline>DUBLIN, April 4</dateline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>LEAD: Ireland is to formally abolish the death penalty and introduce automatic jail sentences of at least 30 years for certain convicted killers, the Government said in a bill published today.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>LEAD: Ireland is to formally abolish the death penalty and introduce automatic jail sentences of at least 30 years for certain convicted killers, the Government said in a bill published today.</p>
        <p>Ireland is to formally abolish the death penalty and introduce automatic jail sentences of at least 30 years for certain convicted killers, the Government said in a bill published today.</p>
        <p>Capital punishment has been retained in Ireland for the killers of policemen, prison officers and foreign leaders and diplomats. For all other killings, it was ended in the late 1950's.</p>
        <p>The bill replaces the death penalty with mandatory 40-year jail sentences. That would mean that, with remission, killers must spend at least 30 years in prison. The bill is expected to pass into law later this year.</p>
      </block>
